CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 14, 1955, pg. 20, reads: "Grill Two Headliners - The crowd-pleasing Deuces Wild, currently filling Crawford Grill Two, at Elmore and Wylie, with sweet music, will be at the popular spot for the next two weeks. They have played successful engagements at many of the city's top clubs.  Presently they have two crazy records going : "Ultra" and "that's All That Matters to Me."  To be released in near future are "Swat Mist" and "I Want a Little Girl," all on the Moss label.  That's Flo Cassinelli on the tenor sax; Don Mastri, bass; Bob Negri, piano, and Spider Rondinelli, drums. - Harris PHoto." on the tenor sax; Don Mastri, bass; Bob Negri, piano, and Spider Rondinelli, drums. - Harris PHoto."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Deuces Wild band wearing matching attire, front row: Flo Cassinelli, Spider Rondinelli; back row: Don Mastri, and Bob Negri, posed in Crawford Grill No. 2
